etymologies: late Middle English (in an earlier sense). Probably from a female forename Gillot (pet form of the female forename Gillian) from Anglo-Norman Gilote, pet form of the female forename Juliane, Giliane

definitions: A woman who is sexually promiscuous or who is flirtatious or coquettish. Also later more generally (sometimes depreciative): a woman or girl, especially one of low social status; a lass. Compare "jill".
